From f71bdeaeac0e8482de869ff0c1a2fec6bae29841 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 21:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add default-disabled GRX-015 Route B rd_native gpu_culling
 in-frame compute cull (R1b: aligned count-dword copy fixes misaligned-clear
 root cause)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Stacked on 0001..0029 + 0040..0045. First rd_native pass that itself issues an
RD::buffer_copy. R1b REVISION of the device-removal root cause
(passes/gpu_culling/rd_native_device_removal_diagnosis.md sec 7): the convicted
cause is a MISALIGNED RenderingDevice::buffer_clear, NOT a same-frame
compute->indirect draw-graph gap. Clearing each surface's instance-count dword at
byte offset (s*command_stride_dwords + instance_count_dword_index)*4 = 4/24/44...
(never a multiple of 16) lowers to RenderingDeviceDriverD3D12::command_clear_buffer,
which builds a RAW buffer UAV (D3D12_BUFFER_UAV_FLAG_RAW, FirstElement = offset/4)
and calls ClearUnorderedAccessViewUint; D3D12 requires a RAW buffer UAV byte offset
to be a multiple of 16 (D3D12_RAW_UAV_SRV_BYTE_ALIGNMENT), so the out-of-spec UAV
removes the device on frame 1 (0x887A0005 — an asynchronous GPU-side fault, silent
under both the debug layer and GPU-Based Validation). Two side-by-side minimal
reproducers isolate it (spike/godot-rurix/upstream-repro/): a bare misaligned
buffer_clear removes the device frame 1, while a pure compute->draw_indirect on a
DISPATCH_INDIRECT buffer runs 300 frames clean. The earlier "general RDG gap" /
live-command-buffer "dual role" attribution is retracted: every prior crashing leg
(shim era, in-graph live buffer, R1 scratch) shared the SAME misaligned count-dword
clear at offset (s*5+1)*4, which was the confounding variable.

R1b keeps R1's Rurix-owned scratch indirect-args decoupling AND fixes the clear:

- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.{h,cpp}: the module still lazily builds the
  pipeline from the Rurix container, buffer_update's the t1 planes, buffer_copy's
  the p_command_bytes live command template into the SCRATCH buffer, binds
  t0=transforms / t1=planes / u0=SCRATCH_commands / u1=visibility, and dispatches
  ceil(instance_count/64). The ONLY change from R1: each surface's SCRATCH
  instance-count dword is now zeroed by an ALIGNED RD::buffer_copy FROM a persistent
  16-byte all-zero SSBO (rd_native_gpu_culling_zero_buffer, created once with
  zero-filled data and NEVER written), not a misaligned RD::buffer_clear.
  buffer_copy lowers to CopyBufferRegion (no RAW-UAV alignment constraint), the
  RD-layer buffer_copy only bounds-checks (a 4-byte offset/size is legal), and it
  is equally draw-graph tracked (add_buffer_copy); the STEP-2 zero copy is a
  write-after-write on the scratch tracker ordered after the STEP-1 template copy,
  so the zero wins over the copied CPU count. The visibility bitmask clear stays a
  buffer_clear at the 16-aligned offset 0 (which never triggered the bug). The live
  MultiMesh command buffer is still only ever a buffer_copy READ source.
- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h, modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp,
  servers/rendering/renderer_rd/forward_clustered/render_forward_clustered.{h,cpp}:
  unchanged control flow; only the diagnostic comments are corrected to the
  misaligned-clear root cause (the "general RDG gap" wording is removed).

The container line (co-located under passes/gpu_culling/artifacts) is UNCHANGED:
the HLSL kernel, the Rurix-owned RTS0, the descriptor layout, the
generate_rd_container.py PASS_REGISTRY entry, and
out/gpu_culling_rd_native.rd_container.bin. R1b changes NO container / b0 / kernel /
RTS0; it only swaps one buffer_clear loop for a buffer_copy loop plus a persistent
zero SSBO.

Fail-closed everywhere: default backend == 0 (and empty container path, or any
allocation/copy/bind/pipeline failure incl. a missing scratch or zero-source
buffer) never engages the cull; a failed record is a no-op (the native CPU-written
command buffer keeps driving the draw). Additive pass — no native Godot compute
pass is replaced. Because the cull is conservative (never culls a visible
instance), the on-screen image is identical to native; only the GPU draw-side
instance count is reduced. R1b ships only after
ci/grx_rb_gpu_culling_rd_native_enablement_smoke.py shows NO device removal on real
hardware; until then real_gpu_pass stays false and the pass stays default-disabled.
RXGD_ABI_VERSION unchanged (no C ABI struct change, no RxGdCaps.flags bit;
bridge-independent). No performance claim is made.

Assisted-by: kiro:claude-opus-4-8
---
 drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h                   |  32 +++
 modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp        |  21 ++
 modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp           | 209 ++++++++++++++++++
 modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.h             |  48 ++++
 .../render_forward_clustered.cpp              | 186 +++++++++++++++-
 .../render_forward_clustered.h                |  19 ++
 6 files changed, 514 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h b/drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h
index dd40ad0..b1ab69a 100644
--- a/drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h
+++ b/drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h
@@ -252,5 +252,37 @@ public:
 	// false so any hooks that do not override this (or the absence of a hooks
 	// singleton) keep the native Godot luminance_reduction + tonemap chain.
 	virtual bool try_record_fused_post_chain_rd_native(RID p_src_color, RID p_lum_source, RID p_prev_luminance, RID p_dst_color, RID p_dst_luminance, Size2i p_source_size, Size2i p_dest_size, float p_exposure, float p_white, float p_luminance_multiplier, float p_min_luminance, float p_max_luminance, float p_exposure_adjust, float p_first_frame, float p_auto_exposure_scale) { return false; }
+	// GRX-015 Route B rd_native gpu_culling (patch 0046, R1b revision): opt-in
+	// in-frame RD-native compute cull hook that drives a RURIX-OWNED scratch
+	// indirect-args buffer, NOT Godot's live MultiMesh command buffer. The first
+	// shipped 0046 wrote the reduced InstanceCount straight into the live
+	// multimesh->command_buffer via a same-frame compute UAV + buffer_clear and was
+	// convicted of device removal (0x887A0005; silent under both the debug layer and
+	// GPU-Based Validation). The corrected root cause (2026-07-13; see
+	// passes/gpu_culling/rd_native_device_removal_diagnosis.md sec 7) is a MISALIGNED
+	// buffer_clear: clearing each surface's count dword at byte offset
+	// (s*stride+index)*4 = 4/24/44... (never a multiple of 16) lowers to a RAW buffer
+	// UAV (D3D12_BUFFER_UAV_FLAG_RAW) + ClearUnorderedAccessViewUint whose byte offset
+	// D3D12 requires to be 16-aligned; the out-of-spec UAV removes the device. It is
+	// NOT a general RDG gap for "a draw-indirect buffer written by compute and consumed
+	// the same frame" — a pure compute->draw_indirect reproducer runs 300 frames clean
+	// while a bare misaligned buffer_clear removes the device frame 1 (both under
+	// upstream-repro/). This R1b hook NEVER touches the live command buffer with
+	// compute/clear: p_commands (the live buffer) is ONLY a buffer_copy READ source;
+	// the module copies the p_command_bytes command template into the caller-owned
+	// p_scratch_commands buffer (a storage_buffer_create with DISPATCH_INDIRECT usage),
+	// zeroes ONLY the SCRATCH buffer's count dwords via an ALIGNED buffer_copy from a
+	// persistent zero buffer (the R1b fix — no misaligned clear), buffer_clear's the
+	// visibility bitmask at the 16-aligned offset 0, binds t0=transforms /
+	// t1=frustum_planes / u0=SCRATCH_commands / u1=visibility, and dispatches
+	// ceil(instance_count/64). The caller then retargets the native indirect draw to
+	// read the scratch buffer. Returning true means the module recorded the in-frame
+	// cull into the scratch buffer (the caller reads scratch for this base); false is a
+	// fail-closed no-op (the native CPU-written command buffer keeps driving the draw).
+	// R1b ships only after the enablement smoke shows NO device removal on real
+	// hardware. The base implementation returns false so hooks that do not override
+	// this (or the absence of a hooks singleton) keep the native CPU-driven command
+	// buffer.
+	virtual bool try_record_gpu_culling_rd_native(RID p_transforms, RID p_commands, RID p_scratch_commands, RID p_visibility, const uint8_t *p_frustum_planes, uint32_t p_frustum_planes_bytes, const uint8_t *p_push_constants, uint32_t p_push_constant_bytes, uint32_t p_instance_count, uint32_t p_surface_count, uint32_t p_command_stride_dwords, uint32_t p_instance_count_dword_index, uint32_t p_visibility_bytes, uint32_t p_command_bytes) { return false; }
 	static D3D12Hooks *get_singleton() { return singleton; }
 };
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
index 23a0f0a..76f1bb2 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp
@@ -394,6 +394,27 @@ void initialize_rurix_accel_module(ModuleInitializationLevel p_level) {
 	// hardcoded to a res:// resource so the smoke/bench harnesses can point at an
 	// absolute staging path.
 	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/fused_post_chain/rd_container_path", "");
+	// GRX-015 Route B rd_native gpu_culling: three-state backend selector for the
+	// gpu_culling pass, INDEPENDENT of the four existing shim settings above
+	// (.../passes/gpu_culling/enabled|dispatch_recording_smoke|dispatch_real_pass|
+	// real_pass_force_capability_downgrade), which are left untouched (the shim
+	// path 0027-0029 keeps its own gate). Values: 0 = disabled (default; nothing
+	// runs here), 1 = shim (nominal; the shim path stays governed by its own
+	// settings), 2 = rd_native (engage the in-frame RD-native compute cull via
+	// try_record_gpu_culling_rd_native, which drives the main RenderingDevice's
+	// buffer_copy -> dispatch -> indirect-draw chain, R1b: the scratch count dwords
+	// are zeroed by an aligned copy, not a misaligned clear). Defaults to 0 so the
+	// shipping build/config never engages the RD-native cull.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/gpu_culling/backend", 0);
+	// GRX-015 Route B rd_native gpu_culling: absolute filesystem path to the Rurix
+	// RenderingShaderContainerD3D12 gpu_culling RD-native container (the 48-byte-b0
+	// variant with the frustum planes as a t1 StructuredBuffer) consumed by
+	// shader_create_from_bytecode when backend == 2. Defaults to empty, which keeps
+	// the RD-native cull fail-closed (no container -> no cull; the native
+	// CPU-driven command buffer keeps driving the indirect draw). Injected here
+	// rather than hardcoded to a res:// resource so the smoke/bench harnesses can
+	// point at an absolute staging path.
+	GLOBAL_DEF_BASIC("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/gpu_culling/rd_container_path", "");
 
 #if defined(D3D12_ENABLED)
 	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/enabled")) {
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
index f5ef657..f0d676c 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
@@ -1801,4 +1801,213 @@ bool RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_record_fused_post_chain_rd_native(RID p_src_color
 	return true;
 }
 
+bool RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_record_gpu_culling_rd_native(RID p_transforms, RID p_commands, RID p_scratch_commands, RID p_visibility, const uint8_t *p_frustum_planes, uint32_t p_frustum_planes_bytes, const uint8_t *p_push_constants, uint32_t p_push_constant_bytes, uint32_t p_instance_count, uint32_t p_surface_count, uint32_t p_command_stride_dwords, uint32_t p_instance_count_dword_index, uint32_t p_visibility_bytes, uint32_t p_command_bytes) {
+	// GRX-015 Route B rd_native gpu_culling (patch 0046, R1b revision): an in-frame
+	// RD-native compute cull that drives a CALLER-OWNED scratch indirect-args buffer
+	// (p_scratch_commands), NOT Godot's live MultiMesh command buffer (p_commands).
+	// This does NOT go through the Rurix rxgd bridge/shim; it drives the main
+	// RenderingDevice directly. The convicted device-removal root cause (corrected
+	// 2026-07-13; see passes/gpu_culling/rd_native_device_removal_diagnosis.md sec 7)
+	// was a MISALIGNED RenderingDevice::buffer_clear: clearing each surface's
+	// instance-count dword at byte offset (s*stride + index)*4 = 4/24/44... (never a
+	// multiple of 16) lowers to a RAW buffer UAV (D3D12_BUFFER_UAV_FLAG_RAW) +
+	// ClearUnorderedAccessViewUint whose byte offset D3D12 requires to be 16-aligned;
+	// the out-of-spec UAV removed the device on frame 1 (0x887A0005, silent under both
+	// the debug layer and GPU-Based Validation). It was NOT a general RDG gap for a
+	// same-frame compute-written draw-indirect buffer: a pure compute->draw_indirect
+	// reproducer runs 300 frames clean, while a bare misaligned buffer_clear removes
+	// the device frame 1 (both under upstream-repro/). R1b keeps R1's scratch
+	// decoupling (p_commands is ONLY a buffer_copy READ source; the compute writes the
+	// caller-owned p_scratch_commands, which the caller retargets the native indirect
+	// draw to read) and additionally replaces the misaligned count-dword clear with an
+	// aligned buffer_copy from a persistent zero buffer (STEP 2), removing the actual
+	// root cause. Every early return keeps the native CPU-driven command buffer
+	// untouched (fail-closed no-op — an additive miss, never a fallback dispatch). The
+	// caller only reaches here when the gpu_culling backend selector is 2 (rd_native).
+	// The enablement smoke's no-device-removal + picture-preserving judgement is the
+	// confirmation, and the pass stays default-disabled until then.
+	RenderingDevice *rd = RenderingDevice::get_singleton();
+	if (rd == nullptr) {
+		return false;
+	}
+	if (rd_native_gpu_culling_load_failed) {
+		// A prior container load / pipeline compile failed; do not retry every
+		// frame. The native CPU-driven command buffer keeps driving the draw.
+		return false;
+	}
+	if (!p_transforms.is_valid() || !p_commands.is_valid() || !p_scratch_commands.is_valid() || !p_visibility.is_valid()) {
+		// p_scratch_commands is the caller-owned scratch indirect buffer the cull
+		// writes and the native draw is retargeted to read; without it, fail closed.
+		return false;
+	}
+	if (p_instance_count == 0 || p_surface_count == 0 || p_command_stride_dwords == 0) {
+		return false;
+	}
+	if (p_command_bytes == 0 || (p_command_bytes % 4u) != 0 || p_command_bytes < p_surface_count * p_command_stride_dwords * (uint32_t)sizeof(uint32_t)) {
+		// buffer_copy/buffer_clear need a dword-multiple scratch size that covers
+		// every surface's 5-dword command block (so all count-dword clears are in
+		// bounds and the full live template is copied).
+		return false;
+	}
+	if (p_frustum_planes == nullptr || p_frustum_planes_bytes != GPU_CULLING_RD_NATIVE_FRUSTUM_PLANES_BYTES) {
+		// The t1 planes payload must be the exact 96-byte / 6x float4 block.
+		return false;
+	}
+	if (p_push_constants == nullptr || p_push_constant_bytes != GPU_CULLING_RD_NATIVE_ROOT_CONSTANT_BYTES) {
+		// The b0 must be the exact 48-byte Rurix-defined block.
+		return false;
+	}
+	if (p_visibility_bytes == 0 || (p_visibility_bytes % 4u) != 0) {
+		// buffer_clear requires a dword-multiple size.
+		return false;
+	}
+	// Lazily build the compute pipeline the first time backend == 2 is exercised:
+	// read the Rurix container bytes, hand them to shader_create_from_bytecode
+	// (-> shader_create_from_container in the D3D12 driver), and create the compute
+	// pipeline. Any failure latches rd_native_gpu_culling_load_failed so it is not
+	// retried per frame.
+	if (!rd_native_gpu_culling_shader.is_valid() || !rd_native_gpu_culling_pipeline.is_valid()) {
+		const String container_path = GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/gpu_culling/rd_container_path");
+		if (container_path.is_empty()) {
+			// No container configured: keep rd_native fail-closed (disabled).
+			rd_native_gpu_culling_load_failed = true;
+			return false;
+		}
+		const Vector<uint8_t> container_bytes = FileAccess::get_file_as_bytes(container_path);
+		if (container_bytes.is_empty()) {
+			rd_native_gpu_culling_load_failed = true;
+			print_verbose(vformat("RurixAccel: rd_native gpu_culling container '%s' missing or empty; native CPU-driven command buffer remains active.", container_path));
+			return false;
+		}
+		const RID shader = rd->shader_create_from_bytecode(container_bytes);
+		if (!shader.is_valid()) {
+			rd_native_gpu_culling_load_failed = true;
+			print_verbose("RurixAccel: rd_native gpu_culling shader_create_from_bytecode failed; native CPU-driven command buffer remains active.");
+			return false;
+		}
+		const RID pipeline = rd->compute_pipeline_create(shader);
+		if (!pipeline.is_valid()) {
+			rd->free_rid(shader);
+			rd_native_gpu_culling_load_failed = true;
+			print_verbose("RurixAccel: rd_native gpu_culling compute_pipeline_create failed; native CPU-driven command buffer remains active.");
+			return false;
+		}
+		rd_native_gpu_culling_shader = shader;
+		rd_native_gpu_culling_pipeline = pipeline;
+		if (!rd_native_gpu_culling_active_logged) {
+			// One-shot marker (NOT per-frame): the RD-native cull is engaged.
+			print_verbose("RXGD_RD_NATIVE_GPU_CULLING active: backend=rd_native, in-frame compute cull engaged (R1b: buffer_copy live->scratch -> aligned buffer_copy zero->scratch count dwords -> dispatch into scratch -> native indirect-draw retargeted to the Rurix scratch buffer; the live MultiMesh command buffer is never compute/clear-touched, and the scratch count zero is an aligned copy not a misaligned clear).");
+			rd_native_gpu_culling_active_logged = true;
+		}
+	}
+	// Lazily create the self-owned 96-byte frustum-planes SSBO (the t1
+	// StructuredBuffer<float4>) and buffer_update it with THIS frame's 6 planes.
+	// buffer_update happens BEFORE compute_list_begin (updating buffers is forbidden
+	// while a compute list is active); the draw graph tracks the update and barriers
+	// it against the compute read.
+	if (!rd_native_gpu_culling_frustum_planes_buffer.is_valid()) {
+		rd_native_gpu_culling_frustum_planes_buffer = rd->storage_buffer_create(GPU_CULLING_RD_NATIVE_FRUSTUM_PLANES_BYTES);
+		if (!rd_native_gpu_culling_frustum_planes_buffer.is_valid()) {
+			// Planes buffer allocation failed: keep the native path (fail-closed).
+			return false;
+		}
+	}
+	// R1b — lazily create the persistent all-zero SSBO used ONLY as the buffer_copy
+	// SOURCE for the per-surface count-dword zeroing in STEP 2. It is created with
+	// zero-filled initial data (resize_initialized zero-fills, and storage_buffer_create
+	// does NOT otherwise zero an empty buffer) and is NEVER written again, so its
+	// 4-byte source region is always 0x00000000. 16 bytes is the RAW-view alignment
+	// quantum and comfortably covers a 4-byte copy. See STEP 2 for why an aligned
+	// buffer_copy replaces the misaligned buffer_clear that was the device-removal
+	// root cause.
+	if (!rd_native_gpu_culling_zero_buffer.is_valid()) {
+		Vector<uint8_t> zero_init;
+		zero_init.resize_initialized(GPU_CULLING_RD_NATIVE_ZERO_BUFFER_BYTES);
+		rd_native_gpu_culling_zero_buffer = rd->storage_buffer_create(GPU_CULLING_RD_NATIVE_ZERO_BUFFER_BYTES, zero_init);
+		if (!rd_native_gpu_culling_zero_buffer.is_valid()) {
+			// Zero-source buffer allocation failed: keep the native path (fail-closed).
+			return false;
+		}
+	}
+	rd->buffer_update(rd_native_gpu_culling_frustum_planes_buffer, 0, GPU_CULLING_RD_NATIVE_FRUSTUM_PLANES_BYTES, p_frustum_planes);
+	// R1b STEP 1 — copy the live command template into the caller-owned scratch
+	// buffer (a READ of p_commands, NOT a compute/clear). This is a graph-tracked
+	// buffer_copy of the full p_command_bytes (all surfaces' 5-dword blocks: the
+	// IndexCountPerInstance / StartIndex / BaseVertex / StartInstance dwords the
+	// draw needs, plus the CPU-written count dword which STEP 2 zeroes). Done BEFORE
+	// compute_list_begin (buffer_copy is a transfer op, forbidden inside a compute
+	// list) and BEFORE the count clear (so the clear wins over the copied count).
+	// The live MultiMesh command buffer is only ever read here; it is never cleared
+	// and never UAV-bound — that dual role was the convicted device-removal hazard.
+	rd->buffer_copy(p_commands, p_scratch_commands, 0, 0, p_command_bytes);
+	// R1b STEP 2 — pre-dispatch zeroing on the SCRATCH buffer only, BEFORE
+	// compute_list_begin (transfer ops are forbidden while a compute list is
+	// active). Zero ONLY each surface's instance-count dword in the SCRATCH buffer
+	// (byte offset (s*command_stride_dwords + instance_count_dword_index)*4; mirrors
+	// the CPU write at mesh_storage.cpp:2210) so the kernel's InterlockedAdd
+	// accumulates from 0; every other command dword in the scratch (dword 0 =
+	// vertices-drawn count, and the StartIndex/BaseVertex/StartInstance dwords)
+	// survives from the STEP-1 copy.
+	//
+	// R1b ROOT-CAUSE FIX (convicted 2026-07-13; see
+	// passes/gpu_culling/rd_native_device_removal_diagnosis.md sec 7): this dword
+	// zero is a graph-tracked buffer_copy FROM the persistent all-zero buffer, NOT a
+	// buffer_clear. buffer_clear lowers to RenderingDeviceDriverD3D12::
+	// command_clear_buffer, which builds a RAW buffer UAV (D3D12_BUFFER_UAV_FLAG_RAW,
+	// FirstElement = p_offset/4) and calls ClearUnorderedAccessViewUint; a RAW buffer
+	// UAV byte offset MUST be a multiple of 16 (D3D12_RAW_UAV_SRV_BYTE_ALIGNMENT). The
+	// count-dword offsets (s*command_stride_dwords + instance_count_dword_index)*4 =
+	// 4/24/44... are NOT 16-aligned, so each misaligned clear produced an out-of-spec
+	// UAV and removed the device on frame 1 (0x887A0005). That misaligned clear — NOT
+	// a general RDG same-frame compute->indirect hazard — was the real root cause
+	// (two side-by-side minimal reproducers under upstream-repro/ isolate it: a bare
+	// misaligned buffer_clear removes the device frame 1, while a pure
+	// compute->draw_indirect runs 300 frames clean). buffer_copy lowers to
+	// command_copy_buffer -> CopyBufferRegion, which has NO RAW-UAV alignment
+	// constraint; the RD-layer buffer_copy only bounds-checks (rendering_device.cpp
+	// buffer_copy) so a 4-byte offset/size is legal, and it is equally draw-graph
+	// tracked (add_buffer_copy). This STEP-2 copy is a write-after-write on the
+	// scratch tracker ordered after the STEP-1 template copy, so the zero wins over
+	// the copied CPU count (the same ordering the STEP-1/clear pair relied on).
+	for (uint32_t s = 0; s < p_surface_count; s++) {
+		rd->buffer_copy(rd_native_gpu_culling_zero_buffer, p_scratch_commands, 0, (s * p_command_stride_dwords + p_instance_count_dword_index) * (uint32_t)sizeof(uint32_t), (uint32_t)sizeof(uint32_t));
+	}
+	// The visibility bitmask clear stays a buffer_clear: its offset 0 IS 16-aligned,
+	// so it never triggered the driver's misaligned-RAW-UAV bug (and clearing the
+	// whole bitmask from 0 is the natural, aligned form).
+	rd->buffer_clear(p_visibility, 0, p_visibility_bytes);
+	// Bind the four structured buffers in the container's binding order: t0 =
+	// src_transforms, t1 = frustum_planes (SRV), u0 = dst_commands = the SCRATCH
+	// buffer (NOT the live p_commands), u1 = dst_visibility (UAV), all as
+	// UNIFORM_TYPE_STORAGE_BUFFER (RAW/structured runtime equivalence — the buffer
+	// probe precedent). UniformSetCacheRD keys on the RID set; the module-owned
+	// planes buffer RID is stable so the cached set stays valid while its CONTENTS
+	// are refreshed each frame via buffer_update. The scratch RID is stable per base
+	// (caller-cached), so its cached set stays valid too.
